<div class="ti_font", style="color: cyan">Question: The 3N-Dimensional Integral in Partition Function of Condensed Matters?</div>
<!-- <div class="r-stack">
     <div class="fragment current-visible"> -->
<p class="page1mathfont">
    \begin{eqnarray}
    \mathcal{Z}&=&\frac{1}{N!h^{3N}}\int d\vec{\textbf{p}}^N\int d\vec{\textbf{q}}^N\exp\{-\beta[\sum_{i=1}^{N}\frac{\vec{\textbf{p}}_i^2}{2m}+U(\vec{\textbf{q}}^N)]\} \\
    &=&\frac{1}{N!}\left(\frac{2\pi m}{\beta h^2}\right)^{\frac{3}{2}N}\int d\vec{\textbf{q}}^N\exp[-\beta U(\vec{\textbf{q}}^N)]
    \end{eqnarray}
    \begin{equation}
    \mathcal{Q}=\int d\vec{\textbf{q}}^N\exp[-\beta U(\vec{\textbf{q}}^N)] \longrightarrow {\text{\color{red} Configurational Integral} (3N\text{-dimensional})}
    \end{equation}
</p>
<p class="ref">
    <span style="color: yellow">Cluster Expansion</span>:
    J.Chem.Phys. <strong>9</strong>,2(1941),
    J.Mol.Liq <strong>224</strong>,694(2016),
    JOM <strong>72</strong>,2226(2021),
    Front.Chem. <strong>8</strong>,757(2020)
</p>
<p class="ref">
